# RELEASE — zsh-manager

Version:  v2.2
Date:     2026-04-19
Platform: openSUSE Tumbleweed
Shell:    zsh 5.9+
Requires: Oh My Zsh, btrfs-progs, snapper

---

## What's in this release

### v2.2 — Btrfs extraction + repo rename zsh-manager (2026-04-19)
- Repo renamed: zsh-snap-man → zsh-manager (GitHub + local)
- Btrfs functions extracted to dedicated plugins (hub-and-plugin architecture):
  - `btrfs-scrub` + aliases → zsh-btrfs-scrub v1.0
  - `btrfs-balance` + `btrfs-balance-threshold` + aliases → zsh-btrfs-balance v1.0
  - `btrfs-health` + `btrfs-snap-size` → zsh-btrfs-health v1.0
- Stubs added for btrfs functions (plugin install guidance)
- snap-help updated to reference dedicated plugins

### v2.1 — Rename snap-man + short aliases + banner
- Renamed plugin and entry point: `btrfs-snapper` → `snap-man`
- `snap-man` — unified interactive menu: list / create / rollback
- Short aliases: `snap-m`, `snap-l`, `snap-n`, `snap-r`, `snap-d`, `snap-c`
- `snap-help` / `man-s` — display all available commands
- Standard banner (CYAN border, version + date, SafeITExperts)

### v2.0 — Modular architecture + English translation
- `snap-list`, `snap-new`, `snap-rollback` extracted to independent plugins
  — stubs remain for backward compatibility when plugins are not loaded
- `snap()` — unified entry point with interactive menu

### Snapshot management (snapper)
- `snap-del <id>` — delete snapshot with usage hint if no argument
- `snap-compare <id1> <id2>` — diff files changed between two snapshots
- `snap-important` / `snap-manual` — filtered views
- Multi-config aliases: `snap-list-root`, `snap-list-home`, `snap-create-root`, `snap-create-home`

### Filesystem maintenance (btrfs)
- `btrfs-scrub` — starts scrub and immediately shows live status
- `btrfs-balance` — configurable dusage/musage thresholds (default 50%)
- `btrfs-balance-threshold` — conditional balance based on actual disk usage
- `btrfs-snap-size` — real space used by snapshots via btrfs qgroup
- `btrfs-health` — aggregated report: usage + device stats + scrub + snapshot summary

### Design decisions
- `btrfs-defrag` intentionally excluded — breaks Copy-on-Write on btrfs
- All functions use `function name { }` syntax
- `rollback-last` provided without confirmation for expert use
